    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nAssuming there is an `exrc`-compatible file in the current directory, if neovim is run with `-u <file>` where `<file>` enables `'exrc'`, or with `nvim -u NORC --cmd 'set exrc'`, the `exrc` file is not executed (nor is a trust prompt displayed).\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n`init.lua`:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.o.exrc = true\r\n```\r\n\r\n`.nvim.lua`:\r\n```lua\r\nprint(\"hi from .nvim.lua\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nRepro: `nvim -u ./init.lua`\r\n\r\nResult: Nothing is printed\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`\"hi from .nvim.lua\"` is printed, or a prompt to trust `\".nvim.lua\"` is displayed\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-1535+g9ecb43b637\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nn/a\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux (`Linux 6.5.11-x64v2-xanmod1-1 GNU/Linux`)\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.30.1\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\ntmux-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nAUR neovim-git",
    "closed_at": "2023-11-23T23:19:07Z",
